bilingual.target: 他给我做了一个木制的玩具。
我喜欢那座木制的小屋。
我喜欢这个木制的相框。
这个木制的桌子很结实。
这些木制的椅子很漂亮。

bilingual.source: The child played with a wooden cube.
bilingual.target: 孩子玩着一个木制的立方体。

bilingual.source: He gave her a wooden jewelry box as a gift.
bilingual.target: 他送给她一个木制的首饰盒作为礼物。

bilingual.source: The restaurant has wooden chairs and tables.
bilingual.target: 这家餐厅有木制的椅子和桌子。

bilingual.source: They built a small wooden cabin in the woods.
bilingual.target: 他们在树林里建了一间小木制的小屋。

list.abstract: wooden，英语单词，主要用作为形容词，意为“木制的；僵硬的，呆板的”。

yingyinNormal.en: What's that? I'll show you. Here it is. It's a wooden box.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是什么？我来演示给你看，就在这儿。这不是一个木箱子吗？

yingyinNormal.en: What's that? I'll show you. Here it is. It's a wooden box.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是什么？我来演示给你看，就在这儿。这不是一个木箱子吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I have one about a toy that I had. A wooden horse. With an inscription underneath.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我记得我原来有个玩具。一个木马玩偶。底部刻了一些字。

yingyinNormal.en: My grandmother used to make this with a big wooden spoon and a big, big bamboo bowl.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我奶奶以前用大木勺和大竹碗来搅拌。

yingyinNormal.en: Why is it called a cuckoo clock? There's a little wooden bird inside called a cuckoo. I've never seen the cuckoo.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么要叫布谷鸟钟呢？因为里面有一只木头鸟 叫作布谷鸟。我从来没见过布谷鸟。

yingyinNormal.en: One second. You know, the Greek version of Mercury, Hermes, was worshipped in Athens by the carving of giant wooden phalluses.
yingyinNormal.zh: 等一下啦。希腊神话中赫耳墨斯，当年在雅典受祭拜时人们是对着巨大的阴茎木雕来祭拜祂。{也就是罗马神话中的墨丘利[水星]}

yingyinNormal.en: But it's a very clever wooden box. I put these peelings in the top and then out of the bottom comes lovely rich earth called compost.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，佩奇。但是你知道吗，这是你一个非常聪明的木箱子。我把这些蔬菜皮倒在上面，然后再箱子的底下就会出现肥沃的泥土。叫做堆肥。

yingyinNormal.en: Or sail into a sea of luxury at Burj Al Arab, a seven star hotel, whose graceful curves echo the traditional wooden vessels of the Gulf.
yingyinNormal.zh: 又或者到迪拜帆船酒店尽享奢华，这间七星级酒店的优美曲线，与波斯湾的传统木伐互相辉映。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, Peppa. But it's a very clever wooden box. I put these peelings in the top and then out of the bottom comes lovely rich earth called compost.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是的，佩奇。但是你知道吗，这是你一个非常聪明的木箱子。我把这些蔬菜皮倒在上面，然后再箱子的底下就会出现肥沃的泥土，叫做堆肥。

yingyinNormal.en: You're right, I can't. You know what? Anyone could rent that apartment now. An opera singer, the cast of stomp. Yeah, a tap-dancing pirate with a wooden leg.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，我不知道，告诉你任何人都可能租那个房，歌剧歌手啦，跺脚舞演员啦，有条木腿的踢踏舞海盗啦。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. Judge all you want to but, married a lesbian, left a man at the altar, fell in love with a gay ice dancer, threw a girl's wooden leg in a fire, living in a box.
yingyinNormal.zh: 随你们怎么批评，娶到女同志，临阵逃婚，爱上同性恋冰上舞者，把女生的木腿丢进火里，关在箱子里。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, the wheat is going to flow down this spout here, if I just pull this little flap out at the top, the mill stones are inside this big wooden box and the grain will get crushed in-between the two stones.
yingyinNormal.zh: 粮食就能顺着一涌而下，如果我把上面的开关打开，粮食就会进到木头盒子里，里面是两块磨石，用来碾碎粮食。
